# Supabase Conventions

## Migrations

File: `supabase/migrations/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`

After migration: `npm run gen:types`

## New org-scoped table checklist

1. Create table in schema (e.g. `app` or extend `administration`)
2. Enable RLS + policies scoped by `organization_id`
3. Create `public.<table>` view with `security_invoker = true`
4. GRANT appropriate permissions on public view
5. Regenerate TypeScript types

## RPC for admin operations

Use `SECURITY DEFINER` when RLS would block legitimate admin actions (e.g. `create_user`, `update_user_roles`, `delete_user`).

## Seed

`supabase/seed.sql` runs on `supabase db reset` (configured in `config.toml`).

Public signup disabled — users created via RPC by admins.
